<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1863" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1863">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11H23/42.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Price</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 514.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 18, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Supplementing my despatch No. 510 of May
                            15 in the case of William T. Harrington, I have the honor to enclose a
                            copy of the Spanish text of the reply from the Panaman Foreign Office, a
                            translation of which was sent with the despatch above mentioned.</p>
                        <p>Unless in the meantime the Department may desire to instruct me specially
                            with reference to the proper response to this note, I shall attempt to
                            answer the arguments presented and assert claim for a definite indemnity
                            in the sum of $5,000.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. Jennings Price.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>